tic\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5831301\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 13, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104tqa1705664057650.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tqa1705664057650.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/tqa1705664057650.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"axq1665702823749\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                             \n Define Date and Time Properties for Languages \n      \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The date and time are often displayed differently in different languages.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"axq1665702823749__context_w4612ab1b5b1_w4613ab1b5_w4614ab1\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"axq1665702823749__note_w4615ab1b5b1b1_w4616ab1b5b1_w4617ab1b5_w4618ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You can also\n            control the formatting of date and time using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NLS_FORMAT</span> and\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$NLS_LOCALE</span>. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fjz1665702531973.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fjz1665702531973.html\" title=\"The language of an application is associated not only with a character set, but with regional conventions for sorting, for expressing numbers, currency, date and time, and so on. The combination of language and region is known as locale.\">Language and Locale</a>. </div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"axq1665702823749__li_d6809e1_d6810e1_d6811e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">More Editors</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Date-time Properties</span></span>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"axq1665702823749__li_d6812e1_d6813e1_d6814e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Select or create the message library to hold the language setup.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"axq1665702823749__li_d6815e1_d6816e1_d6817e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Enter the names of the months in the language for which you are creating the language setup.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"axq1665702823749__li_d6818e1_d6819e1_d6820e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Enter the days of the week in the language for which you are creating the language setup.\n </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"axq1665702823749__note_w4619ab1b5b3b7b3b1_w4620ab1b5b3b7b3_w4621ab1b5b3b7_w4622ab1b5b3_w4623ab1b5_w4624ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Day 1 is Monday.</div>\n</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"axq1665702823749__li_d6821e1_d6822e1_d6823e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"axq1665702823749__p_d13967e1_d13968e1_d13969e1\">Specify a three-letter abbreviation for each day\n               or month. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">It is advisable to use the International Standards Organization (ISO) standards.\n               For example, <code class=\"ph codeph\">SEP</code> is the standard abbreviation for\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">SEPTEMBER</code>.</div>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"axq1665702823749__li_d6824e1_d6825e1_d6826e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"axq1665702823749__p_d13970e1_d13971e1_d13972e1\">Specify the default date, time, and date time\n               display formats.</span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">Click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">&gt;&gt;</span>to select from a list of display formats. The\n                  display format affects how Uniface handles date and time information in\n                  ProcScript. If you do not specify a default, Uniface uses the following default\n                  formats:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"axq1665702823749__li_d6827e1_d6828e1_d6829e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">DD-mmm-YYYY</code> for date. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"axq1665702823749__li_d6830e1_d6831e1_d6832e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">hh:nn:ss</code> for time. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"axq1665702823749__li_d6833e1_d6834e1_d6835e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">dd-mmm-yyhh:nn:ss</code> for date\n                     and time. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5831301\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5831301\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Define Date and Time Properties for Languages Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 13, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Define Date and Time Properties for Languages The date and time are often displayed differently in different languages. Note: You can also control the formatting of date and time using $NLS_FORMAT and $NLS_LOCALE . For more information, see Language and Locale . Choose More Editors > Date-time Properties . Select or create the message library to hold the language setup. Enter the names of the months in the language for which you are creating the language setup. Enter the days of the week in the language for which you are creating the language setup. Note: Day 1 is Monday. Specify a three-letter abbreviation for each day or month. It is advisable to use the International Standards Organization (ISO) standards. For example, SEP is the standard abbreviation for SEPTEMBER . Specify the default date, time, and date time display formats. Click >> to select from a list of display formats. The display format affects how Uniface handles date and time information in ProcScript. If you do not specify a default, Uniface uses the following default formats: DD-mmm-YYYY for date. hh:nn:ss for time. dd-mmm-yyhh:nn:ss for date and time. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}